WEBVTT

00:01.566 --> 00:03.655
Jackson:
Last day of training.

00:03.699 --> 00:05.048
Last day of Tim
barking orders.

00:05.092 --> 00:07.268
Last day that they can fire us
at a moment's notice.

00:07.311 --> 00:10.358
Last day of them recording
every flaw for posterity.

00:10.401 --> 00:12.012
It's kind of
bittersweet.

00:12.055 --> 00:13.361
Nope.
Just sweet.

00:13.404 --> 00:15.058
[ Chuckles ]
Sorry. Sorry.

00:15.102 --> 00:16.581
Guys,
stop apologizing.

00:16.625 --> 00:18.670
You guys have
finally made it,

00:18.714 --> 00:19.671
and I will be
right behind you.

00:19.715 --> 00:21.108
Look, the extra month
will fly by.

00:21.151 --> 00:22.370
You know it.

00:22.413 --> 00:24.589
Now, is Tim gonna do
anything special

00:24.633 --> 00:26.896
to memorialize
your last shift together?

00:26.939 --> 00:28.071
Not knowingly.

00:28.115 --> 00:29.072
You know,
when you move on

00:29.116 --> 00:31.031
from an important
relationship,

00:31.074 --> 00:34.860
there are steps you should take
to ensure a healthy parting.

00:34.904 --> 00:37.602
We are going to work through
every single one of them.

00:37.646 --> 00:39.517
Uh, how, if he doesn't know
you're doing it?

00:39.561 --> 00:41.476
Trickery.
Bye.

00:41.519 --> 00:44.087
That's...
Yeah.

00:44.131 --> 00:45.175
Who are yougonna ride with
today?

00:45.219 --> 00:46.611
No idea.

00:46.655 --> 00:48.961
Grey's busy, and Smitty's
getting a back tattoo.

00:49.005 --> 00:50.789
That's --
Yeah. Don't ask.

00:50.833 --> 00:52.922
So, we are out of TOs,
and I'm guessing

00:52.965 --> 00:54.489
I'm finishing my rookie year
at the front desk.

00:54.532 --> 00:55.664
Huh.
Lopez: Boot.

00:57.927 --> 00:59.102
Where's our gear?

00:59.146 --> 01:01.148
Wait, what?

01:01.191 --> 01:03.019
We started this journey
together.

01:03.063 --> 01:04.325
I think we should end it
that way.

01:04.368 --> 01:05.587
Don't you?

01:05.630 --> 01:06.588
Yeah.

01:06.631 --> 01:08.155
Then let's go.

01:08.198 --> 01:12.072
♪♪

01:12.115 --> 01:13.421
I thought we were tight.

01:13.464 --> 01:14.509
You did?

01:14.552 --> 01:15.553
Um, we are.

01:15.597 --> 01:17.468
That's --
I mean, why? What?

01:17.512 --> 01:19.122
You told
your ethics professor

01:19.166 --> 01:20.732
she should come for
a ride along?

01:20.776 --> 01:21.733
No.

01:21.777 --> 01:22.778
Mm.
We -- No.

01:22.821 --> 01:24.214
We didn't even,
uh, discuss it,

01:24.258 --> 01:25.868
but I-I need to
pass this class,

01:25.911 --> 01:29.045
so it's super important
she doesn't get shot today.

01:29.089 --> 01:30.394
No promises.

01:30.438 --> 01:31.961
You ride with me, you ride
the roller coaster.

01:32.004 --> 01:33.528
Okay, Nyla, I know that --

01:33.571 --> 01:35.312
Hi. Good morning.Good morning.

01:35.356 --> 01:37.401
Uh, Professor Ryan, this is
Detective Nyla Harper,

01:37.445 --> 01:38.620
my training officer.

01:38.663 --> 01:39.621
I'm told
you're gonna be going

01:39.664 --> 01:41.013
on a ride along
with us today.

01:41.057 --> 01:42.711
I hope that's okay.

01:42.754 --> 01:45.017
I didn't want to put you in an
awkward position by asking you,

01:45.061 --> 01:46.932
but your watch commander said
that you'd feel cheated

01:46.976 --> 01:48.238
if I didn't
ride with you, so...

01:48.282 --> 01:50.066
And he was right.

01:50.110 --> 01:51.154
[ Chuckles ]

01:51.198 --> 01:52.155
Uh, shall we?Mm.

01:52.199 --> 01:54.331
Okay.

01:54.375 --> 01:56.159
Harper: So, you, uh,
sign all the paperwork

01:56.203 --> 01:57.508
that says that
we are not liable

01:57.552 --> 01:59.293
if you are maimed
or killed?

01:59.336 --> 02:00.946
I did. It seemed
a bit excessive.

02:00.990 --> 02:02.339
Mm.
No, it's not.

02:02.383 --> 02:04.167
I mean, we will try our best
to protect you,

02:04.211 --> 02:06.952
but we cannot guarantee
your safety.

02:06.996 --> 02:10.173
You will be exposed to all
the same dangers that we are.

02:10.217 --> 02:13.611
Well, more farmers die yearly
than cops do.

02:13.655 --> 02:15.091
I didn't have to sign
a liability waiver

02:15.135 --> 02:16.527
to go apple picking.

02:16.571 --> 02:18.094
That's because you weren't
picking them

02:18.138 --> 02:19.139
out of a wood chipper.

02:19.182 --> 02:20.401
Nolan: Uh, hey,

02:20.444 --> 02:21.924
have you ever seen
a body camera up close?

02:21.967 --> 02:23.055
No.

02:23.099 --> 02:24.405
Well, they're
always running,

02:24.448 --> 02:26.537
uh, until
we actually need them.

02:26.581 --> 02:27.886
We switch them on,
then they start recording,

02:27.930 --> 02:29.279
and they go back
two minutes

02:29.323 --> 02:30.672
so we can catch any of that
last-minute action.

02:30.715 --> 02:32.804
Oh, yet they're
always broken

02:32.848 --> 02:34.850
whenever the cops
cross the line.

02:34.893 --> 02:36.895
You'd be surprised
how many police officers

02:36.939 --> 02:39.028
actually want
a body camera.

02:39.071 --> 02:40.334
Oh.
That way,

02:40.377 --> 02:42.205
it makes it easier to
disprove complaints.

02:42.249 --> 02:44.773
Okay,
then you will not mind

02:44.816 --> 02:47.297
if I record
the ride along myself --

02:47.341 --> 02:48.298
as research tool.

02:48.342 --> 02:49.169
No problem.

02:50.474 --> 02:52.041
[ Chuckles ]

02:52.084 --> 02:53.912
Just as long as you
turn it off

02:53.956 --> 02:56.437
when we hit the strip club
for the lunch buffet.

02:59.266 --> 03:00.528
She's kidding.

03:00.571 --> 03:02.704
That buffet is terrible
at that strip club.

03:02.747 --> 03:04.314
♪ Whoa, oh, oh, oh Ready to go?

03:04.358 --> 03:06.447
♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh

03:06.490 --> 03:11.234
♪ I'm gonna win for you
like I know you want me to do ♪

03:11.278 --> 03:12.496
[ Cameras beeping ]

03:12.540 --> 03:13.976
You got yours on?
Yeah.

03:14.019 --> 03:15.630
Alright.

03:15.673 --> 03:17.240
It's our last shift
together.

03:17.284 --> 03:18.459
It's crazy, huh?

03:18.502 --> 03:19.982
Not really.

03:20.025 --> 03:21.331
Come on.

03:21.375 --> 03:22.593
I mean, we've been ridingshoulder to shoulder

03:22.637 --> 03:24.116
for over a year now.[ Engine starts ]

03:24.160 --> 03:26.075
And soon, there'll be a new
rookie sitting in that seat,

03:26.118 --> 03:28.643
annoying the crap out of me
for 12 hours a day.

03:28.686 --> 03:31.559
So, you're not gonna missriding with me at all?

03:31.602 --> 03:33.256
It's a job,
not happy hour.

03:33.300 --> 03:35.563
Mm. Denial. Check.

03:36.868 --> 03:38.130
What?
Hmm?

03:38.174 --> 03:39.262
Nothing.

03:39.306 --> 03:45.921
♪♪

03:46.965 --> 03:49.664
So, you teach
full time?

03:49.707 --> 03:52.188
No. Just nights
and weekends.

03:52.232 --> 03:54.756
My day job is
civil rights litigation.

03:54.799 --> 03:56.584
And then there's lecturing,
the writing,

03:56.627 --> 03:57.933
the cable news hits.

03:57.976 --> 03:58.934
When do you sleep?

03:58.977 --> 04:00.457
Sleep?
What's that?

04:00.501 --> 04:02.242
Oh, is that what you were doing
in my class on Monday?

04:02.285 --> 04:04.156
[ Chuckles ]
What?

04:04.200 --> 04:05.201
No. Uh, no.

04:05.245 --> 04:06.289
Sometimes, I just --
I hold a blink

04:06.333 --> 04:08.117
for a really long time.

04:08.160 --> 04:09.858
You sure lying to your teacher
is the way to go here?

04:09.901 --> 04:10.989
Actually, now that
I hear it out loud,

04:11.033 --> 04:12.164
I'd like to revise my answer.

04:12.208 --> 04:14.036
Yeah. Uh-huh.[ Chuckles ]

04:14.079 --> 04:16.038
So, uh, given how busy
you are,

04:16.081 --> 04:18.214
why take the time
for a ride along?

04:18.258 --> 04:21.217
Well, I'm finishing up a book
on the future of policing.

04:21.261 --> 04:24.176
Hey, what would you say is
the, uh, biggest challenge

04:24.220 --> 04:26.483
you face day to day?

04:26.527 --> 04:28.616
Finding
a safe bathroom.

04:28.659 --> 04:30.095
Uh, that is --
that is true.

04:30.139 --> 04:32.359
I mean, we can't use a stallbathroom for safety reasons.

04:32.402 --> 04:34.099
The door has to go
floor to ceiling.

04:34.143 --> 04:36.145
And the location of thebathroom, also very important,

04:36.188 --> 04:38.321
so that not a lot of peoplecan see us entering and leaving.

04:38.365 --> 04:39.583
[ Radio static crackles ]

04:39.627 --> 04:40.976
Dispatch: 7-Adam-15,

04:41.019 --> 04:44.109
residential burglary alarm,
1330 Monrovia.

04:44.153 --> 04:46.111
Hundred bucks it's
an accidental trigger.

04:46.155 --> 04:47.461
That is a hard pass.

04:47.504 --> 04:49.376
[ Chuckles ]She's -- She's kidding.

04:49.419 --> 04:51.116
No. No way we'd blow off
a service call.

04:51.160 --> 04:52.117
[ Radio beeps ]

04:52.161 --> 04:53.858
Copy. Responding.

04:53.902 --> 04:55.033
[ Static crackles ]

04:55.077 --> 04:56.426
Lucy: Do you see yourself
as my mentor?

04:57.601 --> 04:59.690
No. I'm your TO.

04:59.734 --> 05:02.214
It's my job to make sure you're
not dangerously incompetent

05:02.258 --> 05:05.087
when you hit the streets withoutsupervision tomorrow.

05:05.130 --> 05:06.262
You know,
when I was a rookie,

05:06.306 --> 05:07.350
I couldn't wait
to get off probation.

05:07.394 --> 05:09.178
Oh, I am excited.

05:09.221 --> 05:10.832
Believe me.

05:10.875 --> 05:14.096
But I also know the importanceof acknowledging your loss

05:14.139 --> 05:16.185
when going throughsomething like this.

05:16.228 --> 05:17.491
"Acknowledging
your loss"?

05:17.534 --> 05:18.970
Hmm.

05:19.014 --> 05:21.451
What is this, some
"Intro to Psych" closure BS?

05:21.495 --> 05:23.279
It's not BS.

05:23.323 --> 05:25.237
It's a widely used
psychological model

05:25.281 --> 05:27.805
to help people cope withthe end of a relationship.

05:27.849 --> 05:29.329
Relationship?

05:29.372 --> 05:31.548
Partnership.
Mentorship.

05:31.592 --> 05:32.767
Whatever you want tocall it.

05:32.810 --> 05:34.246
Look, I don't want to
call it anything.

05:34.290 --> 05:36.074
It's not like you won't see me
tomorrow at the station.

05:36.118 --> 05:37.859
You know, what's there
to talk about?

05:37.902 --> 05:39.339
A lot.

05:39.382 --> 05:41.253
I have a list.

05:41.297 --> 05:42.603
So...
A list?

05:44.909 --> 05:47.608
You know, littering isa $250 fine.

05:47.651 --> 05:50.001
Worth it.

05:50.045 --> 05:51.394
What are you smiling
about?

05:51.438 --> 05:54.397
Well, we were at denial,

05:54.441 --> 05:57.444
but now we have movedto anger.

05:57.487 --> 05:58.880
That's more progress.

06:03.232 --> 06:04.189
Thank you.

06:04.233 --> 06:06.322
[ Radio chatter ]

06:06.366 --> 06:07.541
Gets me out of
the office.

06:07.584 --> 06:09.238
I mean,
not just for today.

06:09.281 --> 06:10.631
I mean, you could have
bounced me from the program

06:10.674 --> 06:12.807
after that first day.

06:12.850 --> 06:14.243
I owe you my career.

06:14.286 --> 06:15.897
♪ I confess,
don't hate the playa... ♪

06:15.940 --> 06:17.812
I'd settle for a sandwich.We're near Phillipe's.

06:17.855 --> 06:19.422
But you just
had breakfast.

06:19.466 --> 06:20.902
You questioning
the pregnant lady?

06:20.945 --> 06:22.294
[ Chuckling ] No, ma'am.
No, ma'am.

06:22.338 --> 06:23.600
What?

06:24.819 --> 06:26.298
You're gonna be a mom.

06:27.038 --> 06:29.258
And?

06:29.301 --> 06:30.912
I don't know.
I mean...

06:30.955 --> 06:34.002
a lot's happened since
we started out together.

06:34.045 --> 06:36.134
I knew my TO would be
important to my career,

06:36.178 --> 06:38.441
but...I don't know.

06:38.485 --> 06:40.138
I didn't realize how important
you'd be to my life.

06:40.182 --> 06:41.792
♪ They might shine,but when they lights go out... ♪

06:41.836 --> 06:44.229
Lay off the sappy stuff.I'm nauseous enough as it is.

06:44.273 --> 06:45.709
[ Chuckles ]

06:47.929 --> 06:48.799
Fiona: Have you read
my work?

06:49.974 --> 06:51.454
I have.

06:51.498 --> 06:52.977
I actually follow you
on social media.

06:53.021 --> 06:54.979
Oh. And?

06:55.023 --> 06:58.069
I'd make a lot of the reforms
you're pushing for,

06:58.113 --> 07:00.332
but some just aren't
based in reality.

07:00.376 --> 07:02.726
Well, maybe not
your reality.

07:02.770 --> 07:04.685
Look, either you want
my opinion or you don't.

07:04.728 --> 07:07.470
If you are just here to confirm
your own point of view,

07:07.514 --> 07:08.819
then I-I will stop
engaging.

07:08.863 --> 07:10.168
No, no, no, no.
That's not what I'm looking for.

07:10.212 --> 07:12.475
I-I'm just used to copstaking my head off

07:12.519 --> 07:14.434
any time I suggestchanging the status quo.

07:14.477 --> 07:15.957
So...
Well, you would be
surprised

07:16.000 --> 07:18.089
how many cops actually know
the system has to change,

07:18.133 --> 07:20.004
but just feel powerless
to make it happen.

07:20.048 --> 07:21.441
Hmm.

07:21.484 --> 07:23.399
[ Door closes ]

07:23.443 --> 07:25.140
Homeowner set off the alarm
accidentally.

07:25.183 --> 07:26.097
Hundred bucks.

07:26.141 --> 07:27.359
Just put it on my tab.

07:27.403 --> 07:29.187
So, you two
getting along? Huh?

07:29.231 --> 07:30.232
My two teachers?

07:30.275 --> 07:31.363
Mm.
Yeah.

07:31.407 --> 07:32.756
We're bonding
by making fun of you.

07:32.800 --> 07:34.802
Oh. Outstanding.Let me get in on that.

07:34.845 --> 07:35.585
Have you noticed
how much I've been

07:35.629 --> 07:37.457
saying "like" lately?

07:37.500 --> 07:39.720
[ Alarm beeping ]

07:39.763 --> 07:40.851
Child abduction.

07:40.895 --> 07:42.940
Suspect is drivinga gold Tacoma truck.

07:42.984 --> 07:44.246
Plate number

07:44.289 --> 07:47.162
2-Queen-Robert-Ida-4-4-5.

07:47.205 --> 07:48.163
Victim was kidnapped from...

07:48.206 --> 07:49.730
City of Angels Hospital.

07:49.773 --> 07:51.209
How old?

07:51.253 --> 07:53.385
Uh...five hours.

07:57.477 --> 07:58.434
Here we go.

07:58.478 --> 08:00.436
[ Engine starts ]

08:00.480 --> 08:03.526
[ Rotor blades whirring ]

08:03.570 --> 08:04.571
Air Three
is lifting now.

08:04.614 --> 08:05.746
I'm 10-9-7.

08:05.789 --> 08:08.836
Searching forthe suspect vehicle.

08:08.879 --> 08:11.795
Uh, newborn baby girlwent missing 20 minutes ago.

08:11.839 --> 08:13.971
The hospital is going overthe surveillance footage.

08:14.015 --> 08:15.843
Wait, don't all babies
get LoJack these days?

08:15.886 --> 08:18.106
Yeah, it was found inthe elevator, cut off.

08:18.149 --> 08:19.760
Who owns the Tacoma?

08:19.803 --> 08:22.240
Uh, that would bethe father -- Jared Young.

08:22.284 --> 08:23.981
Looks like they're going through
a messy divorce.

08:24.025 --> 08:26.244
He was visiting the hospitalearlier that day,

08:26.288 --> 08:27.768
but security had him leave.

08:27.811 --> 08:29.247
There may have beensome kind of threat.

08:29.291 --> 08:31.032
So, what, he went back in
and he just took the baby?

08:31.075 --> 08:32.903
Jared's got quite an extensivecriminal history here.

08:32.947 --> 08:34.818
Lot of narcos --uh, narco possession,

08:34.862 --> 08:37.125
possession to sell,under the influence.

08:37.168 --> 08:38.822
Mm, just the guy you want
taking care of your newborn.

08:38.866 --> 08:40.171
Well, we got the whole citylooking for him.

08:40.215 --> 08:41.172
He won't get far.

08:41.216 --> 08:43.566
So, this baby that the, uh,

08:43.610 --> 08:45.089
whole city is mobilized
to find --

08:45.133 --> 08:46.526
is she by any chance white?

08:48.005 --> 08:49.529
We issue plenty of
Amber Alerts

08:49.572 --> 08:50.965
for children of color,
as well.

08:52.619 --> 08:53.707
Do you have a kid?

08:53.750 --> 08:55.404
Daughter.

08:55.447 --> 08:56.753
And, uh, you're sure
your daughter

08:56.797 --> 08:58.581
would get the same attention
as his son?

08:59.451 --> 09:01.105
From the media? No.

09:01.149 --> 09:05.109
But out here, we --
we look just as hard.

09:05.153 --> 09:06.850
Mrs. Young,this is Detective Lopez.

09:06.894 --> 09:08.765
I'm out heresearching for your baby.

09:08.809 --> 09:09.984
Mrs. Young: [ Voice breaking ]
You have to find her.

09:10.027 --> 09:11.246
Yes, ma'am,we're doing everything we can,

09:11.289 --> 09:12.726
but I need your help.

09:12.769 --> 09:14.554
Is there any place your husbandmight take her?

09:14.597 --> 09:15.729
He lives in Bell Gardens.

09:15.772 --> 09:17.078
Yes, ma'am.

09:17.121 --> 09:18.645
We have officers on the wayto his apartment now,

09:18.688 --> 09:21.517
but if he's not there,
where would he be?

09:21.561 --> 09:24.346
Out buying drugs,
if he has any money.

09:24.389 --> 09:25.826
And if he's not?

09:25.869 --> 09:27.958
Jared will do anything
to get a fix,

09:28.002 --> 09:30.526
including selling our baby.

09:30.570 --> 09:31.788
[ Helicopter blades whirring ]

09:34.225 --> 09:35.662
Gold pickup,
two blocks up.

09:35.705 --> 09:36.619
[ Tires squealing,
engine revving ]

09:36.663 --> 09:40.362
♪♪

09:40.405 --> 09:42.582
Negative.
Texas plates.

09:43.974 --> 09:45.193
Five hours old.

09:45.236 --> 09:46.760
That poor mother must begoing out of her mind.

09:48.805 --> 09:49.850
Let me guess --

09:49.893 --> 09:51.329
you think if the parents
had properly

09:51.373 --> 09:52.809
worked through
their separation,

09:52.853 --> 09:54.245
this whole thing
could have been avoided?

09:54.289 --> 09:58.032
No. Mom needs to get as far awayfrom him as possible.

09:58.075 --> 10:00.338
But I do think that havingeasier access

10:00.382 --> 10:01.775
to counselingand mental health resources

10:01.818 --> 10:03.428
could preventsituations like this.

10:03.472 --> 10:05.692
Sure. But most guys
still wouldn't go.

10:05.735 --> 10:07.302
Yeah, because we stigmatizemental health,

10:07.345 --> 10:10.000
treat it as less importantthan physical health.

10:10.044 --> 10:11.828
It's ridiculous that they teachsex ed in schools,

10:11.872 --> 10:14.352
but not how to be
in a relationship.

10:14.396 --> 10:15.919
I wish someone taught me
how to be in this one.

10:15.963 --> 10:17.486
Oh, so we are
in a relationship.

10:19.706 --> 10:21.577
So, what's the focusof your book?

10:21.621 --> 10:23.666
Uh, reinventing policing --

10:23.710 --> 10:25.276
with a more limited
mandate.

10:25.320 --> 10:26.887
Amen to that.

10:26.930 --> 10:29.019
You agree with taking resourcesaway from police?

10:29.063 --> 10:31.674
If it lessens our load,
then yes, absolutely.

10:31.718 --> 10:33.545
Yeah, we complain about itall the time.

10:33.589 --> 10:35.765
Police have become the catch-allfor the city's problems.

10:35.809 --> 10:40.335
We're expected to be cops,
uh, psychologists,

10:40.378 --> 10:42.859
social workers, teachers,
mediators.

10:42.903 --> 10:44.644
And they only train us
for one of those jobs.

10:44.687 --> 10:46.689
Gold truck.
Two cars ahead.

10:46.733 --> 10:47.429
That's him.

10:49.300 --> 10:50.562
Control, 7-Adam-15.

10:50.606 --> 10:52.782
We have eyes onthe Amber Alert suspect vehicle.

10:52.826 --> 10:55.176
Heading west on Pico,
passing Westlake.

10:55.219 --> 10:58.222
7-Adam-19, inbound on Olympic,passing Ardmore.

10:58.266 --> 11:00.703
7-Adam-07, coming west fromWilshire and Rimpau --

11:00.747 --> 11:02.139
moving to intercept
from the front.

11:02.183 --> 11:04.315
Air Three responding.Heading west from Bell Gardens.

11:04.359 --> 11:06.840
ETA to your location --
approximately six minutes.

11:06.883 --> 11:08.755
Can you parallel suspect
until I get eyes on?

11:08.798 --> 11:09.930
Affirmative.

11:09.973 --> 11:11.192
Parallel?

11:11.235 --> 11:12.802
Yeah, we follow on side streets
and alleyways.

11:15.152 --> 11:16.545
Oh, so he doesn't spot you
and run?

11:16.588 --> 11:18.025
Exactly.
Last thing we want

11:18.068 --> 11:19.722
is him speeding through trafficwith a baby in the car,

11:19.766 --> 11:20.854
especially since
there's no way

11:20.897 --> 11:22.246
he's got an infant car seatin there.

11:22.290 --> 11:23.639
No, we'll just wait untilwe have enough units,

11:23.683 --> 11:24.814
and then we'll
box him in.

11:24.858 --> 11:26.729
Intersection ahead.
We still have him?

11:26.773 --> 11:28.122
Yeah, he's about half a carlength ahead,

11:28.165 --> 11:29.384
but he's speeding up.

11:29.427 --> 11:30.951
He might've seen usbefore we made our turn.

11:30.994 --> 11:32.735
♪♪

11:32.779 --> 11:34.737
7-Adam-19,
Maxwell and Pico.

11:34.781 --> 11:36.521
West of target --waiting for him to pass.

11:40.264 --> 11:42.702
Suspect just went past.Speed -- 50 miles an hour.

11:42.745 --> 11:43.877
We'll move to parallel
on the north.

11:43.920 --> 11:45.095
Copy that.

11:45.139 --> 11:46.401
Why not just set up
a roadblock?

11:46.444 --> 11:48.011
Roadblocks are considereda lethal measure.

11:48.055 --> 11:49.012
Didn't know that.

11:49.056 --> 11:50.187
Yeah,there's a strong chance

11:50.231 --> 11:51.972
a desperate driverwill ram a roadblock.

11:52.015 --> 11:53.277
Clear!

11:53.321 --> 11:54.757
We don't use them unlesswe have no other choice.

11:54.801 --> 11:56.063
Come on, come on.Watch out, watch out!

11:56.106 --> 11:57.673
[ Tires screech ]

11:57.717 --> 11:58.413
I can't see
around the truck.

11:58.456 --> 11:59.631
Move it!
I got it.

11:59.675 --> 12:00.807
Move! Hey!I got it after this car.

12:00.850 --> 12:02.983
Hold on. There we go.Got it.

12:05.420 --> 12:07.465
Do you see him?No.

12:07.509 --> 12:09.816
Well, maybe -- maybe he turned
around when we got stuck.

12:09.859 --> 12:11.469
7-Adam-19,
we've lost visual.

12:11.513 --> 12:12.775
You got eyes on him?

12:12.819 --> 12:14.734
Negative.We haven't reacquired visual.

12:14.777 --> 12:16.692
Where the hell
is that airship?

12:16.736 --> 12:18.825
Pilot: Air Three is overhead.
Arriving on scene.

12:18.868 --> 12:20.652
What's the suspect's 20?

12:20.696 --> 12:22.654
We lost visual.
Pico, east of Maxwell.

12:22.698 --> 12:24.874
It's possible he turned off andheaded either north or south.

12:24.918 --> 12:26.528
Copy that.
We're gonna orbit.

12:26.571 --> 12:31.533
♪♪

12:31.576 --> 12:33.100
Contact.

12:33.143 --> 12:34.928
Suspect vehicle now heading
north on Livingston.

12:34.971 --> 12:36.625
Repeat,
north on Livingston.

12:36.668 --> 12:38.322
Copy. On our way.

12:38.366 --> 12:40.672
Speed is
approximately 65.

12:40.716 --> 12:41.717
Looks like he's heading
for the freeway.

12:41.761 --> 12:44.067
[ Tires screech ]

12:46.635 --> 12:47.723
Hold on.

12:47.767 --> 12:49.420
Suspect just sideswiped
another vehicle.

12:49.464 --> 12:51.074
He's lost control.

12:51.118 --> 12:53.250
[ Car crashes ]

12:53.294 --> 12:54.817
Tell me that wasn't
our guy.

12:54.861 --> 12:56.427
He just TC'd into
a telephone pole.

12:56.471 --> 12:58.429
Can you see
inside the truck?

12:58.473 --> 12:59.691
Negative.

13:01.041 --> 13:02.390
[ Helicopter blades whirring ]

13:02.433 --> 13:04.609
[ Tires squealing ]

13:09.092 --> 13:10.441
[ Brakes screech ]

13:11.616 --> 13:12.661
Harper: Hands!Nolan: Police!

13:15.272 --> 13:16.926
Show me your hands!

13:16.970 --> 13:18.145
Where is your daughter?

13:18.188 --> 13:19.668
Jared: What?

13:19.711 --> 13:21.452
Nolan: Keep your hands
where we can see them.

13:25.674 --> 13:27.110
No kid.
There's no kid in here!

13:27.154 --> 13:28.285
There's no kid!

13:28.329 --> 13:29.678
Your baby,
where is she?

13:29.721 --> 13:31.158
At the hospital
with her mom.

13:31.201 --> 13:32.246
Lucy:
Then why did you run?

13:32.289 --> 13:33.813
Tim: Gun and drugs.

13:36.163 --> 13:37.773
Fiona: If he doesn't have
the baby, who does?

13:43.039 --> 13:44.040
[ Helicopter blades whirring ]

13:44.084 --> 13:45.476
Never thought
I'd be disappointed

13:45.520 --> 13:47.827
a meth-head wasn't
taking care of a newborn.

13:47.870 --> 13:49.132
But I guess there's still
plenty of time

13:49.176 --> 13:50.960
for him to mess up
this kid's childhood,

13:51.004 --> 13:52.135
once we get her back.

13:53.310 --> 13:54.355
Ifwe get her back.

13:54.398 --> 13:56.357
[ Radio chatter ]

13:56.400 --> 13:58.750
You know, whenever you need
Halloween costumes

13:58.794 --> 14:00.230
for Lopez Jr.,

14:00.274 --> 14:02.711
my mom has dozens
in storage.

14:02.754 --> 14:05.583
I'm talking cop uniforms
for every age.

14:05.627 --> 14:07.324
You never really wanted to beanything else?

14:09.109 --> 14:11.459
Astronaut? Ninja?

14:11.502 --> 14:12.852
Ninja astronaut?
[ Chuckles ]

14:12.895 --> 14:15.637
I mean, that'd be cool,
but...mnh-mnh.

14:15.680 --> 14:16.681
No.

14:16.725 --> 14:18.945
I guess I just
wanted to be my dad.

14:18.988 --> 14:21.077
It was like my way of
feeling close to him

14:21.121 --> 14:22.122
when he wasn't around.

14:22.165 --> 14:24.298
Was that a lot?
Yeah.

14:24.341 --> 14:26.866
I mean, he was a detective
when I was born,

14:26.909 --> 14:29.259
trying to make a name
for himself.

14:29.303 --> 14:31.087
Lot of long hours.

14:31.131 --> 14:32.306
But you were close.

14:32.349 --> 14:33.960
Yeah, eventually.

14:34.003 --> 14:36.919
Mom was kind of on her own
until I was 12.

14:36.963 --> 14:39.226
And that's when he moved up,
got more stable hours.

14:39.269 --> 14:40.967
Mm.

14:41.010 --> 14:44.144
I mean,
I always loved him --

14:44.187 --> 14:46.929
don't get me wrong --
even when he wasn't around.

14:46.973 --> 14:50.063
I have a lot of
great memories, you know?

14:50.106 --> 14:51.629
Of course.

14:51.673 --> 14:54.458
You know, you and Wesley are
going to be awesome parents.

14:54.502 --> 14:56.591
I know.

14:56.634 --> 14:58.201
It's just...

14:58.245 --> 15:00.247
We both get so wrapped up
in our cases,

15:00.290 --> 15:03.380
we barely make timeto have dinner together.

15:03.424 --> 15:05.121
How are we supposed tomake time for a kid?

15:05.165 --> 15:08.298
Wesley is loaded.
You get yourself a nanny.

15:08.342 --> 15:09.734
Or three.

15:09.778 --> 15:11.040
So a stranger
can raise my child?

15:11.084 --> 15:12.302
I mean,
it won't be a stranger

15:12.346 --> 15:14.870
when you get to know them,
you know?

15:14.914 --> 15:17.046
Look, you are not
the first detective

15:17.090 --> 15:19.179
to have to balance work
with a kid.

15:19.222 --> 15:20.571
Talk to Harper
about how she did it.

15:22.182 --> 15:25.098
Lopez: Harper, can you ten-three
to a backup channel?

15:26.838 --> 15:29.406
Sure, go to 11.
Don't record this.

15:30.320 --> 15:31.626
[ Camera clicks off ]

15:33.497 --> 15:35.847
I need you to give methe reals on something.

15:35.891 --> 15:37.153
How difficult was it
to go back to work

15:37.197 --> 15:38.589
after Lila was born?

15:39.895 --> 15:41.157
Honestly,
I barely remember.

15:41.201 --> 15:42.942
I almost died
giving birth, so...

15:44.073 --> 15:46.902
But, uh, that's -- that's not
gonna happen to you.

15:46.946 --> 15:51.037
G-Giving birth can be
a wonderful experience,

15:51.080 --> 15:53.343
I've been told.

15:53.387 --> 15:54.562
Definitely get
the epidural.

15:54.605 --> 15:56.912
Don't worry.
I'm not a lunatic.

15:56.956 --> 15:59.219
I'm thinking of scheduling a C,but I'm worried

15:59.262 --> 16:00.611
that the stitches
and everything

16:00.655 --> 16:03.136
will keep me off workeven longer.

16:03.179 --> 16:05.007
I worried about the same thing,but you know what?

16:05.051 --> 16:06.269
I got stitches anyway --

16:06.313 --> 16:08.097
just not in my stomach.

16:08.141 --> 16:09.751
Okay. Change us back
to channel one.

16:09.794 --> 16:11.666
Wh-- I-I-- I thinkI want to hear this.

16:13.059 --> 16:14.799
Tell me the truth --

16:14.843 --> 16:16.671
Am I gonna poop myself?

16:16.714 --> 16:18.368
And I'm out.

16:18.412 --> 16:19.500
Wow.

16:19.543 --> 16:20.631
[ Chuckles ]

16:20.675 --> 16:22.242
I wish I could say no.

16:22.285 --> 16:24.157
Why can't we just do thattwilight sleep thing

16:24.200 --> 16:25.593
they did back in the '50s?

16:25.636 --> 16:27.029
[ Chuckles ]
I asked.

16:27.073 --> 16:29.858
Apparently it is
"grossly unethical."

16:29.901 --> 16:32.556
Sgt. Grey: Detectives,
are you done?

16:32.600 --> 16:33.557
Both: Yes, sir.

16:38.649 --> 16:41.739
We must seem callous,
joking while a kid is missing.

16:41.783 --> 16:43.045
No, I get it.
I'm sure it's hard

16:43.089 --> 16:45.091
to work
these kinds of cases.

16:45.134 --> 16:46.831
Calls involving kidsare the worst.

16:46.875 --> 16:48.181
You can't help but think,what if they were mine?

16:48.224 --> 16:49.269
Mm.

16:49.312 --> 16:50.313
Yeah,
I don't have kids,

16:50.357 --> 16:52.359
but I feel the same way

16:52.402 --> 16:54.578
every time another Black kid
gets shot by police.

16:56.363 --> 16:58.017
[ Computer beeps ]

16:59.018 --> 17:01.585
Oh. Hospital sentthe video of the kidnapping.

17:03.326 --> 17:04.719
You can't see her face.

17:06.503 --> 17:07.896
Lopez:
That is just terrifying.

17:07.939 --> 17:09.898
A stranger
snatching your baby

17:09.941 --> 17:11.073
when you're not thereto protect them.

17:11.117 --> 17:12.379
Don't worry.

17:12.422 --> 17:14.076
I will personally
stand watch over your kid

17:14.120 --> 17:15.208
until you leave
the hospital.

17:15.251 --> 17:16.774
You better.

17:16.818 --> 17:18.428
Do they have an ID
on the kidnapper?

17:18.472 --> 17:19.342
Not yet.

17:19.386 --> 17:20.735
Listen to me.

17:20.778 --> 17:23.694
We're gonna find her,
alright?

17:23.738 --> 17:25.174
And that baby's
gonna be fine.

17:25.218 --> 17:26.480
You'll see.

17:26.523 --> 17:29.787
[ Helicopter blades whirring ]

17:31.876 --> 17:33.269
We don't have time
for this.

17:33.313 --> 17:35.402
Every minute we waste waitingfor an ID on this woman

17:35.445 --> 17:36.925
is a minute she could behurting this kid --

17:36.968 --> 17:38.274
or worse.

17:38.318 --> 17:39.275
Look, you need to
get your head right

17:39.319 --> 17:40.233
in case this goes bad.

17:40.276 --> 17:42.104
I'm squared away.

17:42.148 --> 17:45.064
The fact that you just said that
means you're not.

17:46.369 --> 17:48.067
Look, you've been lucky
on the job so far.

17:49.590 --> 17:51.548
No. Alright.

17:51.592 --> 17:54.508
I'm sorry. That --
That came out wrong.

17:54.551 --> 17:55.900
You've been through Hell --

17:55.944 --> 17:58.512
stuff that would've broken
a lot of veteran cops.

17:58.555 --> 18:01.080
But a dead kid
is different.

18:01.123 --> 18:04.039
A dead kid
changes you forever.

18:05.562 --> 18:06.781
[ Sighs ]

18:06.824 --> 18:09.218
I really hopeour last shift together

18:09.262 --> 18:10.524
doesn't end with that.

18:10.567 --> 18:13.222
Yeah. Me too.

18:13.266 --> 18:14.528
[ Radio chatter ]

18:14.571 --> 18:16.530
Okay, so what's next
on your list?

18:19.620 --> 18:23.276
[ Inhales sharply ]
Okay.

18:23.319 --> 18:24.668
"Surround yourself with people

18:24.712 --> 18:27.149
who support, value,
and energize you,"

18:27.193 --> 18:30.239
which...may have to waituntil later.

18:30.283 --> 18:32.850
Then, uh, "Reflect onthe lessons learned --

18:32.894 --> 18:36.463
both the good and the bad --and express gratitude."

18:37.812 --> 18:39.944
Okay.

18:39.988 --> 18:42.556
So, what have I taught you
that you're grateful for?

18:42.599 --> 18:44.601
Um...hmm.

18:46.429 --> 18:49.258
Not to second-guess
myself.

18:49.302 --> 18:51.304
Yeah, early on,

18:51.347 --> 18:54.481
one look from youcould send me into a tailspin.

18:54.524 --> 18:55.917
Plain Clothes Day.
Mm-hmm.

18:55.960 --> 18:57.962
But I've learned to trustmy instincts,

18:58.006 --> 19:00.704
even if they go againstwhat you would do,

19:00.748 --> 19:02.880
which will be crucialfor undercover work.

19:04.795 --> 19:06.797
You serious about
being UC?

19:06.841 --> 19:08.930
Yeah.

19:08.973 --> 19:10.714
Why? Do you not think
I'm tough enough?

19:10.758 --> 19:12.455
No, it's not about
being tough.

19:12.499 --> 19:14.718
I mean, look,
you're as tough as they come.

19:14.762 --> 19:18.679
It's just
you're...sensitive.

19:19.680 --> 19:20.811
[ Scoffs ]
You are!

19:20.855 --> 19:22.770
Look what happened
with Tamara.

19:22.813 --> 19:26.034
You gave her your car,
for crying out loud.

19:26.077 --> 19:27.340
And today --

19:27.383 --> 19:30.081
today, this whole need
to relive the last year,

19:30.125 --> 19:31.300
talk about
our feelings.

19:31.344 --> 19:33.694
I happen to thinkthat caring about people,

19:33.737 --> 19:36.914
connecting with them,is what makes me a good cop.

19:36.958 --> 19:38.133
It does.

19:38.177 --> 19:39.830
Just not a good UC.

19:39.874 --> 19:41.615
Look, to work undercover,

19:41.658 --> 19:44.705
you have to be able to lie
to someone's face --

19:44.748 --> 19:46.315
make them believe
you're their best friend

19:46.359 --> 19:49.231
and then stab them
in the back.

19:49.275 --> 19:51.277
I just don't think you have
that killer instinct.

19:54.193 --> 19:56.151
Ouch.

19:56.195 --> 19:57.457
I'm sorry.

19:57.500 --> 19:59.198
But it's better
you hear it now.

19:59.241 --> 20:02.723
[ Radio chatter,
siren wailing in distance ]

20:06.117 --> 20:08.859
You're right.

20:08.903 --> 20:11.253
And I appreciate
your honesty.

20:11.297 --> 20:12.863
You always tell me
the truth,

20:12.907 --> 20:15.083
no matter how painfulit's gonna be,

20:15.126 --> 20:17.259
and you deserve the samefrom me.

20:21.089 --> 20:26.007
I've been struggling withbeing honest with you all day.

20:26.050 --> 20:30.054
I've been hiding behindthis stupid closure checklist,

20:30.098 --> 20:32.100
trying to get up the courageto tell you something.

20:33.841 --> 20:35.321
Okay.

20:35.364 --> 20:36.409
What?

20:44.155 --> 20:45.766
I have feelings
for you.

20:50.249 --> 20:52.686
Uh, like f--Look, we've been througha lot this year.

20:52.729 --> 20:57.125
I mean...
you saved my life.

20:57.168 --> 20:59.519
And I didn't want tosay anything before

20:59.562 --> 21:02.565
because I didn't want toput you in a weird position.

21:02.609 --> 21:06.308
But now, I mean,
I think...

21:06.352 --> 21:09.877
I think the reason why you'reso protective of me and --

21:09.920 --> 21:11.966
and why you don't want meto be an undercover cop

21:12.009 --> 21:13.446
is because...

21:15.752 --> 21:17.450
...because you havefeelings for me, too.

21:20.496 --> 21:21.758
Lucy, I --

21:21.802 --> 21:24.761
No, listen, I-I know
it's complicated.

21:24.805 --> 21:26.459
You're my TO.

21:26.502 --> 21:28.461
You're responsible
for me.

21:28.504 --> 21:33.030
I know that you would nevercross that line, but...

21:33.074 --> 21:38.122
starting tomorrow, I guess...you're not,

21:38.166 --> 21:40.037
and I...

21:40.081 --> 21:41.561
Uh -- Eh --

21:44.346 --> 21:46.305
First of all...

21:46.348 --> 21:48.307
I-I just, like --

21:50.309 --> 21:51.092
Thank you.

21:51.135 --> 21:54.443
Um...you're...

21:55.792 --> 21:57.794
Look, Lucy,
I'm -- I'm flattered.

21:57.838 --> 22:01.276
I am.

22:01.320 --> 22:03.452
You're a great girl.

22:03.496 --> 22:05.149
Woman. Woman.

22:05.193 --> 22:09.153
And I...

22:09.197 --> 22:10.546
Um...

22:10.590 --> 22:11.591
[ Sighs ]

22:11.634 --> 22:13.897
Crap.

22:13.941 --> 22:14.898
Listen.

22:14.942 --> 22:17.727
[ Laughing ]

22:19.642 --> 22:21.470
Are you kidding me?!

22:21.514 --> 22:23.429
I'm sorry!

22:23.472 --> 22:24.386
Are you kidding me?

22:24.430 --> 22:25.474
Wait, I'm sorry.

22:25.518 --> 22:26.301
Oh, you're sorry.

22:26.345 --> 22:28.216
Wait. Just wait.

22:28.259 --> 22:30.436
Lie to your face --
check.

22:30.479 --> 22:32.263
Make you thinkI've fallen for you --

22:32.307 --> 22:33.743
double check.

22:33.787 --> 22:35.702
Oh, and stab you
in the back

22:35.745 --> 22:37.268
when you thinkwe're best friends --

22:37.312 --> 22:38.748
triple check.

22:38.792 --> 22:40.141
Look me in the face...

22:40.184 --> 22:41.360
Nope.
...and tell me

22:41.403 --> 22:43.579
you don't thinkI have the killer instinct

22:43.623 --> 22:45.407
to do undercover work.

22:45.451 --> 22:47.061
Look me in my face.

22:47.104 --> 22:48.497
♪♪

22:52.327 --> 22:55.374
[ Radio chatter ]

23:02.163 --> 23:05.079
It's weird now,
isn't it?

23:05.122 --> 23:06.428
Nope.

23:07.647 --> 23:09.431
I was just
making a point.

23:09.475 --> 23:11.520
And you're undermining it
by feeling guilty.

23:18.745 --> 23:20.007
Harper:
You're out of your mind.

23:20.050 --> 23:21.791
You want to try
the Camden Experiment

23:21.835 --> 23:22.966
in Los Angeles?

23:23.010 --> 23:24.446
I'm sorry. What's
the Camden Experiment?

23:24.490 --> 23:26.579
Uh, fire
all police officers,

23:26.622 --> 23:28.232
make them reapply
for their jobs.

23:28.276 --> 23:29.451
Oh, just that?

23:29.495 --> 23:31.801
[ Chuckles ]
Well, you're both good cops.

23:31.845 --> 23:33.760
You'd be back on the force
in no time.

23:33.803 --> 23:36.893
But running new backgroundchecks on every single officer,

23:36.937 --> 23:39.200
most especially combing through
their social media posts --

23:39.243 --> 23:40.419
that'll get rid of
most of the problem.

23:40.462 --> 23:42.551
We'd be coming back to
a gutted force.

23:42.595 --> 23:45.293
I mean,
you would be down 10%.

23:45.336 --> 23:46.990
Maybe 20%.

23:47.034 --> 23:49.819
But you would be coming back to
a betterforce.

23:49.863 --> 23:51.168
And what about the kid
that goes missing

23:51.212 --> 23:52.474
the day we're all fired?

23:52.518 --> 23:55.172
I mean, it wouldn't happen
overnight.

23:55.216 --> 23:58.132
It would happen gradually,
in stages.

23:58.175 --> 24:02.484
But without major action,
things will neverget better.

24:02.528 --> 24:04.268
Sgt. Grey: 7-Adam-15,

24:04.312 --> 24:06.096
we have a possible suspect ID
on the Amber Alert.

24:06.140 --> 24:08.447
Last name Cissane,
first name Rita.

24:08.490 --> 24:10.579
Suspect's husband called 911.

24:10.623 --> 24:12.494
Make contact
to take his statement.

24:12.538 --> 24:14.540
Address is being sent
to your box.

24:14.583 --> 24:16.542
Copy that. We got it.
On our way.

24:19.022 --> 24:21.329
Ethan: Yeah, if, uh --
i-if she reaches out,

24:21.372 --> 24:24.898
um, please, please,
please, please call me.

24:24.941 --> 24:27.466
Um...okay. Yeah, no.
I-I gotta go.

24:30.599 --> 24:32.688
Mr. Cissane,
I'm Detective Harper.

24:32.732 --> 24:34.342
This is Officer Nolan.

24:34.385 --> 24:37.606
I understand that your wife,
Rita, was here with a baby?

24:37.650 --> 24:39.652
Yeah, I-I don't --
I don't know where she is.

24:39.695 --> 24:43.177
I-I tried calling
everyone that I know.

24:43.220 --> 24:44.918
I-I tried to stop her
from leaving,

24:44.961 --> 24:48.617
but she was holding that baby,
and it was...just so little.

24:48.661 --> 24:51.402
I know. They can look
so fragile at that age.

24:51.446 --> 24:52.839
Uh, tell us about
your wife.

24:52.882 --> 24:55.232
Is there anything that could
have precipitated this?

24:55.276 --> 24:58.105
You don't know?

24:58.148 --> 25:02.762
W-We lost our daughter, Casey,
this morning to SIDS.

25:02.805 --> 25:05.765
Rita went into the nursery
to check on her,

25:05.808 --> 25:09.290
and then I heard screaming,
so I ran in,

25:09.333 --> 25:13.816
and she was so still...
s-so cold.

25:13.860 --> 25:17.254
I am so sorry.
Sir, h-how old was she?

25:17.298 --> 25:18.778
[ Crying ] Two months.

25:18.821 --> 25:21.084
That's why your wife was
at the hospital today?

25:21.128 --> 25:23.565
Yeah, we -- we raced Casey
to the Emergency Room,

25:23.609 --> 25:25.741
hoping that they could do
something, but it was --

25:25.785 --> 25:27.569
it was too late.

25:27.613 --> 25:32.269
And then there was so many, uh,
questions and -- and forms.

25:32.313 --> 25:36.535
It took me a while to realize
that, um, that Rita had left.

25:36.578 --> 25:38.624
She wasn't answering her cell,
so I thought maybe s-she --

25:38.667 --> 25:41.104
she came home,
but she wasn't here,

25:41.148 --> 25:43.803
and then she just showed up
like nothing had happened,

25:43.846 --> 25:47.241
and she was just...
holding this little baby

25:47.284 --> 25:49.852
and calling her Casey

25:49.896 --> 25:51.201
and saying that everything had
been a big mistake.

25:51.245 --> 25:52.333
[ Sniffles ]

25:52.376 --> 25:53.856
Okay, uh, we're gonna
have to initiate

25:53.900 --> 25:55.641
Child Death Protocol.

25:55.684 --> 25:57.077
Treat the place
like a crime scene.

25:57.120 --> 26:00.820
Notify Homicide,
the District Attorney, and CPS.

26:00.863 --> 26:02.735
Wait, wait, wait, wait.
We didn't kill our daughter.

26:02.778 --> 26:03.649
It was -- It was --
It was SIDS.

26:03.692 --> 26:05.781
Yes, sir.
I understand.

26:05.825 --> 26:08.001
I'm not saying that we believe
that you harmed your child,

26:08.044 --> 26:09.959
but we do have protocols
we have to follow.

26:10.003 --> 26:12.048
Eh, sir, it's --
the hard fact is

26:12.092 --> 26:13.876
what most people consider
to be SIDS

26:13.920 --> 26:16.575
is actually accidental
suffocation

26:16.618 --> 26:19.055
from soft bedding
or a toy.

26:19.099 --> 26:22.276
Uh, right now, we have to
focus on your wife.

26:22.319 --> 26:24.147
Is there anywhere you think
she might have gone?

26:24.191 --> 26:25.453
I don't know.

26:25.496 --> 26:26.846
I've reached out to everyone
I can think of,

26:26.889 --> 26:29.413
but she's not really
herself right -- right now.

26:29.457 --> 26:31.459
Has she been depressed
lately?

26:31.502 --> 26:33.635
Yeah. I mean, she hasn't been
eating or sleeping.

26:33.679 --> 26:36.420
The doctor said she had,
um...PPD,

26:36.464 --> 26:38.466
but Rita refused any help.

26:38.509 --> 26:40.337
Uh, has she been
drinking a lot?

26:40.381 --> 26:41.817
Any drugsor medication?No.

26:41.861 --> 26:44.211
No, the doctor prescribed
antidepressants,

26:44.254 --> 26:46.648
but Rita wouldn't take them.
I'm just so scared that --

26:46.692 --> 26:48.345
Thank you, sir.Okay, thank you.

26:48.389 --> 26:49.999
Please don't hurt her.

26:50.043 --> 26:51.566
She's not herself right now.[ Car doors open, close ]

26:51.610 --> 26:53.437
You have to promise me that
you won't hurt her, please.

26:54.917 --> 26:56.397
[ Engine starts ]

26:56.440 --> 26:58.704
[ Sobbing ]

26:58.747 --> 27:02.621
♪♪

27:07.103 --> 27:09.018
Updated Amber Alert.

27:09.062 --> 27:11.281
New suspect vehicle isa green Ford Fiesta.

27:11.325 --> 27:14.850
License plate3-Paul-Charles-Ida-0-2-6.

27:14.894 --> 27:16.983
Suspect is Rita Cissane.

27:17.026 --> 27:20.073
31-year-old white femalewho lost her baby to SIDS.

27:23.859 --> 27:26.253
This case is all the nightmaresin my closet combined.

27:26.296 --> 27:28.647
I know. Sorry.

27:28.690 --> 27:30.823
How am I ever gonna let my kid
out of my sight?

27:30.866 --> 27:32.825
With all the things we seeon the job,

27:32.868 --> 27:34.261
the -- the things I knowabout people --

27:34.304 --> 27:37.046
Look, the things we see
are outliers.

27:37.090 --> 27:40.267
Look, every day, we show up
on people's worst day.

27:40.310 --> 27:42.443
We see the exception,
not the rule.

27:42.486 --> 27:45.098
I know that up here,but --

27:45.141 --> 27:49.232
Look, whether the kid is with
you or Wesley or a nanny,

27:49.276 --> 27:50.843
they'll be fine, okay?

27:50.886 --> 27:53.715
It's just so differentfrom the way I grew up.

27:53.759 --> 27:55.978
Wesley was raised
by a nanny.

27:56.022 --> 27:59.721
But when my mom went to work,she put me in the back room,

27:59.765 --> 28:02.855
and the other womenwould check in on me.

28:02.898 --> 28:05.858
Can't exactly drop off Lopez Jr.in Holding every morning.

28:05.901 --> 28:07.381
[ Chuckles ]
I don't know.

28:07.424 --> 28:09.252
Smitty is
surprisingly maternal.

28:09.296 --> 28:10.776
[ Chuckles ]

28:10.819 --> 28:13.648
That is the most horrifying idea
I've ever heard...

28:13.692 --> 28:15.737
and I want it to bea reality show so bad.

28:15.781 --> 28:18.000
Right? I would watch
the hell out of that.

28:19.001 --> 28:21.525
Rita is negativeon any previous 5150 holds,

28:21.569 --> 28:23.963
and there are no registeredfirearms in her name.

28:24.006 --> 28:25.312
If this woman's doctor couldn't
get through to her,

28:25.355 --> 28:26.617
how will you?

28:26.661 --> 28:27.749
I-I mean,
this woman is in crisis.

28:27.793 --> 28:29.185
She needs a psychiatrist.

28:29.229 --> 28:30.578
Yeah, but the baby
needs a cop.

28:30.621 --> 28:32.754
The honest truth is wedon't have enough information

28:32.798 --> 28:34.103
to know what
we're dealing with.

28:34.147 --> 28:35.714
But that's every call.

28:35.757 --> 28:37.367
It's a constant struggleto figure things out

28:37.411 --> 28:38.891
before it's too late.

28:41.328 --> 28:43.373
Uh, 7-Adam-19,
go to channel nine.

28:44.331 --> 28:45.941
Go for 7-Adam-19.

28:45.985 --> 28:47.726
Did you studypostpartum depression

28:47.769 --> 28:49.118
in your psych major?

28:49.162 --> 28:53.514
Yeah. PPD is fairly common,affects 1 in 8 new moms.

28:53.557 --> 28:56.038
In most cases, they feel tired,
alone, guilty.

28:56.082 --> 28:57.692
Some feel a lack of attachmentand then guilt

28:57.736 --> 28:58.998
for not feeling attached.

28:59.041 --> 29:03.002
Some are overwhelmed by paranoia --

29:03.045 --> 29:07.397
visions of horrible thingshappening to their own child.

29:07.441 --> 29:10.139
I see Rita turned downtreatment.

29:10.183 --> 29:12.489
That tells me she's probably  dealing with shame,

29:12.533 --> 29:14.622
trying to cope alone,isolating.

29:14.665 --> 29:16.189
Now add to that
the trauma

29:16.232 --> 29:18.495
of finding her childunresponsive.

29:18.539 --> 29:20.280
That could precipitatea mental break.

29:20.323 --> 29:22.543
If it's an extreme case of PPD,which is rare,

29:22.586 --> 29:25.328
she could be thinking aboutharming herself or her baby.

29:25.372 --> 29:26.634
Tim. Green Fiesta.

29:26.677 --> 29:27.809
Plates match.
That's our car.

29:27.853 --> 29:28.810
Nolan, we found
Rita's car.

29:28.854 --> 29:31.508
21000 block of Manningham.

29:31.552 --> 29:33.641
On our way.
Let's go.

29:33.684 --> 29:35.686
♪♪

29:38.167 --> 29:39.603
Lucy: Control, 7-Adam-19,

29:39.647 --> 29:41.997
we've located the Fiesta from
the revised Amber Alert.

29:42.041 --> 29:44.608
21000 block of Manningham.

29:44.652 --> 29:46.610
[ Pleasant music plays
on stereo]No sign of suspect or child.

29:49.439 --> 29:51.441
It's still hot.
She must have just ditched it.

29:51.485 --> 29:53.400
Man: Hey. You looking
for the driver?

29:53.443 --> 29:54.880
Tim: Yeah, you see
where she went?

29:54.923 --> 29:57.143
Nah. I was walking by
when she parked on the curb.

29:57.186 --> 29:59.145
How long ago?About five minutes.

29:59.188 --> 30:00.581
Enough time for Butch and I
to circle the block.

30:00.624 --> 30:03.062
Did she have
a baby with her?
No idea.

30:03.105 --> 30:05.629
I just watched her
totally demolish
that parking spot.

30:05.673 --> 30:07.283
[ Laughs ] Reminded me
of my ex-wife.

30:07.327 --> 30:08.937
Uh, yes, sir.
Please call us

30:08.981 --> 30:10.852
if you remember
anything else.
Okay.

30:10.896 --> 30:13.159
Control, 7-Adam-19, I got
the vehicle, unoccupied.

30:13.202 --> 30:15.161
Witness says the suspect hereless than five minutes ago.

30:15.204 --> 30:16.336
She's on foot.

30:16.379 --> 30:17.685
We need backup
and an airship

30:17.728 --> 30:18.773
to secure
a 10-block radius

30:18.817 --> 30:19.992
for a grid search.

30:21.602 --> 30:22.908
♪♪

30:22.951 --> 30:24.039
I don't like this.

30:24.083 --> 30:25.084
She wouldn't have abandoned
the car

30:25.127 --> 30:26.607
unless she stopped
for a reason.

30:26.650 --> 30:28.261
Odds are it won't be
a good one.

30:28.304 --> 30:29.915
We gotta find her fast.

30:33.788 --> 30:35.790
This is crazy.

30:35.834 --> 30:37.183
There's no way we find her
and the baby in time.

30:37.226 --> 30:39.315
We've got multiple units
and an airship searching.

30:39.359 --> 30:40.273
We will find them.

30:40.316 --> 30:41.752
How? They could be
anywhere.

30:41.796 --> 30:43.885
No. On foot with a newbornand a five-minute head start,

30:43.929 --> 30:45.582
she's definitely withinour grid.

30:45.626 --> 30:47.019
Someone will have seen her.

30:47.062 --> 30:50.457
Just...pray we find her beforeshe does something rash.

30:50.500 --> 30:59.727
♪♪

30:59.770 --> 31:00.815
Up on the right.

31:00.859 --> 31:03.078
[ Siren chirps ]

31:05.080 --> 31:07.126
Not her.

31:10.303 --> 31:11.478
Can I make a suggestion?

31:11.521 --> 31:12.914
Of course.

31:12.958 --> 31:14.829
Would it be helpful to have
Rita's husband

31:14.873 --> 31:18.050
brought down here
for -- for when she's found?

31:18.093 --> 31:19.573
That could be
dangerous.

31:19.616 --> 31:21.575
We don't know what the situationwas like at the house,

31:21.618 --> 31:24.012
and even if the baby's death
truly was accidental,

31:24.056 --> 31:25.840
there could have been
marital issues

31:25.884 --> 31:27.494
that added to Rita's PPD.

31:27.537 --> 31:29.191
We'd be introducing
a wildcard

31:29.235 --> 31:30.540
to an already tenuoussituation.

31:30.584 --> 31:32.151
Wait, so it's all on you?

31:32.194 --> 31:34.370
I mean, no matter what you find
when you get to her,

31:34.414 --> 31:35.502
you have to be ready to
deal with it?

31:35.545 --> 31:38.157
What -- What if you make
a mistake?

31:38.200 --> 31:39.985
We have to live with it.

31:40.028 --> 31:42.596
If we can.

31:42.639 --> 31:45.207
Pilot: All units, Air Three has
eyes on the suspect.

31:45.251 --> 31:46.295
Fourth Street Bridge.

31:46.339 --> 31:49.037
Repeat --
Fourth Street Bridge.

31:49.081 --> 31:51.257
She has the baby.
She's standing at the railing.

31:51.300 --> 31:53.824
Possible jumper.
Repeat, possible jumper.

31:53.868 --> 31:55.130
Here we go.

31:55.174 --> 31:57.263
Control, advise Fire we have
a possible jumper

31:57.306 --> 31:58.394
on Fourth Street Bridge.

31:58.438 --> 31:59.700
See if they havea crash pad available.

31:59.743 --> 32:03.051
We'll also need RA andbackup units, Code 2 high.

32:03.095 --> 32:09.362
♪♪

32:09.405 --> 32:12.278
[ Helicopter blades whirring ]

32:15.542 --> 32:17.370
[ Car doors close ]

32:17.413 --> 32:19.285
Maybe I should
stay back.

32:19.328 --> 32:20.677
Uh, it's up to you,

32:20.721 --> 32:22.070
but a friendly face
not in uniform

32:22.114 --> 32:23.854
might actually calm
the situation.

32:23.898 --> 32:25.291
How do you want to
play this?

32:25.334 --> 32:26.031
You go talk to her.

32:26.074 --> 32:27.336
You sure?

32:27.380 --> 32:28.947
Yeah, I'll step in
if I need to.

32:31.645 --> 32:34.561
W-Why -- Why Nolan?

32:34.604 --> 32:38.217
He has a way of connecting with
people in crisis situations.

32:38.260 --> 32:40.610
Hi, Rita.

32:40.654 --> 32:41.698
I'm John.

32:41.742 --> 32:42.699
[ Baby crying ]

32:42.743 --> 32:44.266
How do you know
my name?

32:44.310 --> 32:45.659
Uh, Ethan told me.

32:45.702 --> 32:48.053
He's very worried
about you.

32:48.096 --> 32:50.011
I'm fine.

32:50.055 --> 32:51.970
Who's that
you got there?

32:52.013 --> 32:53.275
Casey.

32:53.319 --> 32:54.581
This is Casey.

32:54.624 --> 32:56.017
Oh.

32:56.061 --> 32:57.714
Casey looks
a little bit cold.

32:57.758 --> 32:59.673
Why don't we bring her inside,
off the bridge?

32:59.716 --> 33:00.587
No.

33:00.630 --> 33:03.068
She's fine with
her mama.

33:03.111 --> 33:05.157
Do you mind if I just
make sure?

33:05.200 --> 33:06.375
Stay back.

33:06.419 --> 33:07.420
Okay, yeah.
I'll stay back.

33:07.463 --> 33:08.769
We -- We can just talk.

33:17.386 --> 33:18.170
Lucy: How's she doing?

33:18.213 --> 33:20.302
Uh, it's touch and go.

33:20.346 --> 33:22.000
What do you need?Keep them back.

33:22.043 --> 33:23.740
We don't want to
spook her.

33:23.784 --> 33:25.742
Okay.Nolan: No, I know it can
feel isolating,

33:25.786 --> 33:27.440
being a parent to
a newborn...

33:27.483 --> 33:28.571
She's not looking at
the baby.

33:28.615 --> 33:30.312
Nolan:
...so much to learn.

33:30.356 --> 33:32.010
[ Baby fusses ]You never feel like
what you're doing...

33:32.053 --> 33:33.576
She's trying to
convince herself

33:33.620 --> 33:35.317
that it's her baby
she's holding.

33:35.361 --> 33:37.928
Yeah. Deep down inside,
she knows it's not.

33:37.972 --> 33:40.018
What happens when
she figures out the truth?

33:40.061 --> 33:41.671
It's hard to say
for sure.

33:41.715 --> 33:43.195
It could break the spell or it
could send her over the edge,

33:43.238 --> 33:44.544
literally.

33:44.587 --> 33:46.328
Control, what's the ETA
on Fire?

33:46.372 --> 33:47.590
Dispatch: Three minutes.

33:47.634 --> 33:49.157
Might as well be
three hours.

33:49.201 --> 33:51.551
Nolan: Are you thirsty,
Rita?

33:51.594 --> 33:52.247
I can get you
some water.

33:52.291 --> 33:53.814
Nolan.

33:53.857 --> 33:55.294
Can I talk to her?

33:55.337 --> 33:56.469
Hey, Rita, I'm gonna
introduce you

33:56.512 --> 33:57.992
to my friend,
Angela, okay?

33:58.036 --> 33:59.472
Okay.

33:59.515 --> 34:00.995
Hi, Rita.

34:01.039 --> 34:03.084
I'm here to help.

34:03.128 --> 34:04.129
Is this Casey?

34:05.478 --> 34:07.045
Yes.

34:07.088 --> 34:08.524
I love that name.

34:08.568 --> 34:12.311
My fiancé and I can't agree
on a name for our baby.

34:12.354 --> 34:13.921
How did you choose?

34:13.964 --> 34:16.097
I don't know.

34:16.141 --> 34:18.230
When she was born, she just
looked like a Casey.

34:18.273 --> 34:21.102
[ Baby fussing ]

34:21.146 --> 34:22.756
How far along are you?

34:22.799 --> 34:24.497
14 weeks.

34:24.540 --> 34:27.108
I'm already scared
about giving birth.

34:27.152 --> 34:28.283
The pain.

34:28.327 --> 34:30.590
Don't worry about
the pain.

34:30.633 --> 34:34.289
Once they put your baby
in your arms

34:34.333 --> 34:37.727
and you look down into
those beautiful eyes,

34:37.771 --> 34:39.555
it was all worth it.

34:39.599 --> 34:43.124
I heard all newborns
have blue eyes.

34:43.168 --> 34:44.647
Not Casey.

34:44.691 --> 34:48.042
Dark brown,
right from the start.

34:48.086 --> 34:50.784
The most amazing
head of hair.

34:50.827 --> 34:51.654
I hope
if I have a daughter,

34:51.698 --> 34:53.439
she's born with hair.

34:53.482 --> 34:56.442
My cousin's little girl,
she was bald

34:56.485 --> 34:58.487
for like the first
18 months.

34:58.531 --> 35:00.141
Everyone thought
she was a boy.

35:00.185 --> 35:01.403
I love putting

35:01.447 --> 35:03.884
Casey's hair
in little pigtails.

35:03.927 --> 35:07.757
She always fights me,
but she looks so cute.

35:07.801 --> 35:12.153
Rita, can you do something
for me?

35:12.197 --> 35:13.763
Can you look at Casey?

35:13.807 --> 35:15.896
Just look in those pretty,
brown eyes.

35:15.939 --> 35:18.377
[ Baby crying ]

35:18.420 --> 35:19.421
No.

35:19.465 --> 35:20.596
Please, Rita.

35:20.640 --> 35:22.337
I need you to
look in her eyes.

35:22.381 --> 35:24.426
[ Helicopter blades whirring ]

35:27.951 --> 35:30.606
[ Crying continues ]

35:32.391 --> 35:35.959
It's not Casey,
is it?

35:36.003 --> 35:37.961
[ Voice breaking ] No.

35:38.005 --> 35:40.138
No.

35:40.181 --> 35:42.792
Here. I got her.

35:42.836 --> 35:45.491
I'll get her back to
her mother, okay?

35:49.103 --> 35:51.453
Tell her [Sniffles]
I'm sorry.

35:53.673 --> 35:55.065
Nolan:
Thank you, Rita.

35:55.109 --> 35:57.242
That was a very brave thingyou did,

35:57.285 --> 35:59.287
and now I need youto come with me, okay?

36:00.593 --> 36:02.899
My baby died.

36:02.943 --> 36:04.336
I know.

36:04.379 --> 36:05.511
I'm so sorry.

36:05.554 --> 36:07.730
[ Sobbing ]

36:07.774 --> 36:11.647
Come on. Come on.

36:13.519 --> 36:15.999
[ Baby cooing ]

36:16.043 --> 36:23.311
♪♪

36:29.274 --> 36:31.711
[ Engine shuts off ]

36:31.754 --> 36:33.669
Well, thank you
for today.

36:33.713 --> 36:35.976
This is an experience
I will not forget.

36:36.019 --> 36:38.108
Well, we should schedule

36:38.152 --> 36:40.067
another one of theselittle ride alongs

36:40.110 --> 36:41.895
so that we can continuethe conversation.

36:41.938 --> 36:43.505
Oh, that won't be
necessary.

36:43.549 --> 36:44.637
[ Camera clicks off ]

36:44.680 --> 36:47.205
The book's already written,
isn't it?

36:47.248 --> 36:49.119
I sent it to my publisher
last week.

36:49.163 --> 36:50.599
Mm.
What?

36:50.643 --> 36:52.122
Then what was today about,
then?

36:52.166 --> 36:54.168
Just an anecdote
for the book tour?

36:54.212 --> 36:56.562
No, I didn't know the day was
gonna end up the way it did.

36:56.605 --> 36:58.520
But how do you write a book
about policing

36:58.564 --> 36:59.608
without having seen it
up close?

36:59.652 --> 37:01.610
Oh, I have seen it.
Believe me.

37:01.654 --> 37:03.133
Today may have been
my first ride along,

37:03.177 --> 37:04.222
but it was not my first time

37:04.265 --> 37:05.788
sitting in the back seat
of a cop car.

37:05.832 --> 37:08.138
I see, but if you're going to
fix an engine,

37:08.182 --> 37:09.792
don't you think it would be
helpful to look under the hood?

37:09.836 --> 37:12.012
That is a flawed analogy,
Officer Nolan,

37:12.055 --> 37:13.492
because a car is not
actively trying to

37:13.535 --> 37:14.710
keep you from fixing it.

37:16.103 --> 37:17.452
Uh, excuse me.

37:19.759 --> 37:22.762
Look, I get that the path
to real change

37:22.805 --> 37:24.764
seems almost impossible.

37:24.807 --> 37:27.723
I mean, police departments are
pros at circling the wagons

37:27.767 --> 37:30.291
when public opinion
turns against them.

37:30.335 --> 37:33.076
But I promise you,

37:33.120 --> 37:35.427
the only way
things really will change

37:35.470 --> 37:37.820
is if cops get on board.

37:37.864 --> 37:39.257
I agree.

37:39.300 --> 37:41.694
But cops only act when activists
make so much noise,

37:41.737 --> 37:43.304
they cannot be ignored.

37:43.348 --> 37:44.827
Like in Camden.

37:44.871 --> 37:47.177
Look, you're talking to
two police officers

37:47.221 --> 37:48.831
who would like to
see things change,

37:48.875 --> 37:51.834
and we're not the only ones at
the station that feels this way.

37:51.878 --> 37:55.316
I just think that...
uh, maybe you could benefit

37:55.360 --> 37:57.753
from some of our insights.

38:01.931 --> 38:02.802
Alright.

38:04.020 --> 38:05.674
You sold me.

38:05.718 --> 38:07.676
Great.
I'll tell Sergeant Grey.

38:07.720 --> 38:09.243
I'm sure he'd love to
be part of the conversation.

38:09.287 --> 38:10.853
Oh, thank you.

38:10.897 --> 38:13.726
And thank you both for
the ride along.

38:13.769 --> 38:15.336
I will see you in class.

38:15.380 --> 38:16.642
Looking forward.

38:19.732 --> 38:22.604
I think that went well,
all things considered.

38:22.648 --> 38:24.780
Oh, yeah. No, she's definitely
gonna give you an "A."

38:24.824 --> 38:26.608
-You think?
-No.

38:26.652 --> 38:28.349
She is gonna make you earn it
in class,

38:28.393 --> 38:29.698
like the rest of
her students.

38:29.742 --> 38:31.221
Fair enough.
Yeah.

38:31.265 --> 38:32.701
You have any plans for
the rest of the night?

38:32.745 --> 38:34.921
Hugging my daughter
until she is sick of it

38:34.964 --> 38:36.923
and then hugging hersome more.
Sounds nice.

38:36.966 --> 38:37.924
Nolan.

38:39.534 --> 38:41.101
I'll see you tomorrow.Alright.

38:41.144 --> 38:42.929
Sir.
Well?

38:42.972 --> 38:44.539
How'd it go
with Professor Ryan?

38:44.583 --> 38:46.149
Good, I think.

38:46.193 --> 38:48.021
She's gonna be calling you to
talk about, uh, police reform --

38:48.064 --> 38:49.283
for her book.

38:49.327 --> 38:51.372
[ Chuckles ]

38:51.416 --> 38:53.766
You point her my way to get back
at me for the ride along?

38:53.809 --> 38:54.810
No, sir. No.

38:54.854 --> 38:55.811
I just know
how committed you are

38:55.855 --> 38:57.900
to making things better.

38:57.944 --> 39:00.294
Even if it does mean having to
admit you're wrong to do it.

39:00.338 --> 39:02.383
Oh. Uh, I'm sorry?

39:03.515 --> 39:05.691
When was I ever wrong?

39:05.734 --> 39:08.998
Well, nothing comes to
mind off hand.

39:09.042 --> 39:11.784
I guess there was that one time
you said if I succeeded,

39:11.827 --> 39:14.352
your house would be
"flooded with middle-aged losers

39:14.395 --> 39:18.530
looking for an 'Eat Pray Love'
path to reinvention."

39:18.573 --> 39:20.836
I wrote it down.

39:20.880 --> 39:23.839
You haven't succeeded yet,
Officer Nolan.

39:23.883 --> 39:26.233
Yes, sir.

39:26.276 --> 39:26.973
Good night, sir.

39:27.016 --> 39:29.410
Good night.

39:29.454 --> 39:31.412
Lopez: Can't wait to get out
of this uniform.

39:31.456 --> 39:32.935
Hey, thanks again for
riding with me.

39:32.979 --> 39:34.154
Are you kidding me?

39:34.197 --> 39:35.895
I wouldn't have missed it
for the world.

39:35.938 --> 39:38.376
And now
it's end of shift,

39:38.419 --> 39:40.813
and you are no longer
a rookie.

39:40.856 --> 39:42.292
[ Exhales deeply ]

39:42.336 --> 39:43.946
How does it feel?

39:43.990 --> 39:45.992
Unreal.

39:46.035 --> 39:48.124
I mean, everything in my life
has been geared towards

39:48.168 --> 39:52.607
getting me to this moment,
and...now it's here.

39:52.651 --> 39:54.392
Kinda can't believe it,
to be honest.

39:54.435 --> 39:57.525
Well, congratulations.

39:57.569 --> 39:59.222
You earned it.

39:59.266 --> 40:00.485
♪ I couldn't see the forest
for the trees ♪

40:00.528 --> 40:03.444
♪ Too many empties on the side

40:03.488 --> 40:05.925
♪ But I kept trading all
my cigarettes for sunsets ♪

40:05.968 --> 40:06.969
♪ Now I'm getting richer
all the time ♪

40:07.013 --> 40:08.841
We did it.

40:08.884 --> 40:10.712
No. Youdid it.

40:13.411 --> 40:14.934
What's this?

40:14.977 --> 40:17.545
It's a copy of
your final evaluation.

40:17.589 --> 40:19.460
I wrote it
before our shift today.

40:19.504 --> 40:21.854
Like Plain Clothes Day.

40:21.897 --> 40:23.812
Only this time,
I didn't have to rewrite it.

40:23.856 --> 40:25.466
Mm.

40:25.510 --> 40:26.772
♪ I'll be young before I die

40:26.815 --> 40:28.469
"Officer Chen impressed me

40:28.513 --> 40:30.471
with every decision she made
today.

40:30.515 --> 40:32.604
I will miss
riding with her."

40:32.647 --> 40:34.344
♪ I'll be wrong before
I'm right ♪

40:34.388 --> 40:37.870
♪ I keep filling up
my crowded heart, yeah ♪

40:37.913 --> 40:40.220
You don't let anyone
ever tell you

40:40.263 --> 40:42.440
you can't do something.

40:42.483 --> 40:44.180
Not even me.

40:44.224 --> 40:45.747
♪ Now all I see is the beauty
of the thunderstorm ♪

40:45.791 --> 40:47.183
Yes, sir.

40:47.227 --> 40:48.271
♪ Let it wash it all away [ Inhales deeply ]

40:48.315 --> 40:51.666
Step five -- acceptance.

40:51.710 --> 40:54.495
Our checklist is complete.
[ Chuckles ]

40:54.539 --> 40:56.845
Um...I have
a gift for you.

40:58.238 --> 41:00.719
It's a thank-you.

41:00.762 --> 41:03.156
For every lesson
I had to learn.

41:03.199 --> 41:05.767
Uh, should I open it now?

41:05.811 --> 41:06.986
Absolutely.

41:07.029 --> 41:07.726
Mm-hmm.

41:07.769 --> 41:08.988
Okay.

41:09.031 --> 41:10.468
♪ I'll be dumb before I'm wise

41:10.511 --> 41:12.208
[ Pop ]

41:12.252 --> 41:13.558
♪ I'll be wrong
before I'm right ♪[ Chuckles ]

41:13.601 --> 41:14.733
[ Exhales sharply ]

41:14.776 --> 41:17.344
[ Laughs ]
It's been a blast, sir.

41:17.387 --> 41:20.303
I'll see you tomorrow...Lucy.

41:21.479 --> 41:23.393
See you tomorrow, Tim.[ Door opens ]

41:23.437 --> 41:24.960
♪ I will laugh and I will cry [ Door closes ]

41:25.004 --> 41:26.788
[ Chuckles ]

41:26.832 --> 41:27.833
Ready to celebrate?

41:27.876 --> 41:29.791
You know it.
[ Chuckles ]

41:29.835 --> 41:33.839
So, yeah. It was
the perfect way to end the year.

41:33.882 --> 41:35.057
[ Indistinct conversation ]

41:35.101 --> 41:36.058
Exactly.

41:36.102 --> 41:37.495
Where you going?

41:39.018 --> 41:40.889
Uh, home.

41:40.933 --> 41:42.891
No, you're not.

41:42.935 --> 41:44.980
You are coming to dinner
with Lila and me.

41:45.024 --> 41:47.505
Uh, that's -- that's very nice
of you, but I'm okay.

41:47.548 --> 41:49.071
No, you're not.

41:49.115 --> 41:51.160
You feel like a failure
because they're moving on

41:51.204 --> 41:52.988
and you're not.

41:53.032 --> 41:55.251
But you will.

41:55.295 --> 41:56.775
I appreciate that,
but you, uh,

41:56.818 --> 41:59.125
certainly don't have to take me
to dinner out of pity.

41:59.168 --> 42:01.344
It's not pity
when you're paying.

42:01.388 --> 42:02.607
♪ I'll keep filling up...

42:02.650 --> 42:04.260
W-Well, how can I say no
to that?

42:04.304 --> 42:06.132
You can't.

42:06.175 --> 42:07.829
I'm gonna go pick up
Lila.

42:07.873 --> 42:10.745
Reservation is under my name
at Mercado.

42:10.789 --> 42:13.356
And I expect a skinny margarita
waiting when I get there.

42:13.400 --> 42:14.227
Yes, ma'am.
Mm-hmm.

42:14.270 --> 42:16.272
And, um...

42:16.316 --> 42:17.273
Thank you.

42:17.317 --> 42:18.492
You're welcome.

42:20.233 --> 42:20.712
[ Car door closes ]

42:24.846 --> 42:27.762
--Captions by VITAC--

